# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Units
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:unit-3362
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can citizens bring about change?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-citizens-bring-about-change" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils explore the different ways citizens can take action and what
  role this plays in democracy."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about the role of citizens and groups in shaping and
  improving communities. Pupils build on their foundational knowledge of democracy, rights and
  equity as they explore different methods of democratic participation and influencing change.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3362-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3362-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3362-3 ;
  curric:id "3362"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.458142Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-active-citizenship-making-a-positive-difference .

oakcurric:unit-3355
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How does the political system work in the UK?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-does-the-political-system-work-in-the-uk" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn about the roles of government and parliament and how
  they are organised. They explore how elections work and what the role of political parties
  and MPs are."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about how the political system works in the UK as they build
  their awareness of democracy and government. Understanding the structure and function of the
  UK political system is crucial for their development as informed citizens. This knowledge
  helps them grasp how political decisions are made within parliamentary democracy, the checks
  and balances within different branches of government, and the importance of citizen
  participation in elections and democracy.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3355-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3355-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3355-3 ;
  curric:id "3355"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.515705Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

oakcurric:unit-3002
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Citizenship - what's it all about?"@en ;
  curric:slug "citizenship-whats-it-all-about" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils consider what citizenship is all about, they will explore what
  knowledge and skills they need to develop to become active citizens."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides an introduction to some of the key citizenship concepts
  that pupils will study throughout their citizenship journey. Building on knowledge from the
  primary curriculum, students consider their existing knowledge on concepts such as democracy,
  rights and responsibilities and active citizenship and explore how this knowledge will be
  expanded through studying citizenship.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3002-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3002-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3002-3 ;
  curric:id "3002"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.634132Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law ,
    oakcurric:thread-active-citizenship-making-a-positive-difference .

oakcurric:unit-3371
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Can digital democracy increase political participation?"@en ;
  curric:slug "can-digital-democracy-increase-political-participation" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider what a digital citizen is and how the digital world can be used to
  increase political engagement, examining cases of how digital democracy has worked across
  the globe."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Exploring digital democracy now helps pupils understand how digital tools
  can enhance political participation and engagement. This unit is timely as it prepares pupils
  to navigate rights related issues, and contribute to the evolving digital political
  landscape, empowering them to be informed and active citizens. By learning these concepts
  early, pupils can effectively participate in democratic processes, making this education
  relevant and impactful.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3371-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3371-2 ;
  curric:id "3371"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.741013Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-role-of-media-and-digital-democracy .

oakcurric:unit-3360
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What is the law and how is it changed?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-is-the-law-and-how-is-it-changed" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils explore what the law is and how criminal and civil laws are
  made. They examine what role citizens can have in changing the law and consider how the
  justice system should apply to young people."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about what the law is and how it is changed because they are
  beginning to understand the structure of society and their role within it. Understanding the
  legal system and the process of lawmaking is crucial for their development as informed
  citizens. This knowledge helps them grasp the importance of laws, how they evolve to reflect
  societal values, and how individuals and groups can influence legal change, preparing them
  for active participation in their communities.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3360-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3360-2 ;
  curric:id "3360"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.051257Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3363
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Why was the struggle for the vote important today?"@en ;
  curric:slug "why-was-the-struggle-for-the-vote-important-today" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils analyse how political rights have changed over time considering important
  campaigns such as the fight for female suffrage. They examine why voting matters and
  consider what role they can have in democracy prior to being eligible to vote."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about the struggle for the vote because it is essential to
  understand the foundations of modern democracy, equality and representation. Understanding
  the historical context highlights the value of democracy and how it develop and changes over
  time. This knowledge helps them appreciate the significance of voting rights, active
  citizenship and change, and fosters an awareness of the importance to pursue equity.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3363-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3363-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3363-3 ;
  curric:id "3363"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.163763Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3368
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Are people treated equally in UK society?"@en ;
  curric:slug "are-people-treated-equally-in-uk-society" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils examine what discrimination is and how the law protects people against it,
  and consider what we can do to create a fairer society and how the UK has progressed in
  terms of equality."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their understanding of rights and communities from Year 7 and
  8, pupils in Year 9 learn about whether people are treated equally in UK society as they
  deepen their awareness of social justice, inclusion and equity. This knowledge helps them
  recognize discrimination including different racism, appreciate and value diversity, and
  advocate for a fairer society.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3368-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3368-2 ;
  curric:id "3368"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.185201Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3366
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How is the UK governed?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-is-the-uk-governed" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils explore the difference between local, regional and national governance and
  compare the political systems in the UK and US."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their knowledge from Year 7 and 8 about the political system
  and the law, pupils in Year 9 learn about how the UK is governed as they develop political
  literacy. Understanding the structure of the UK government, including the roles of
  Parliament, the Prime Minister, and the judiciary, is crucial for their development as
  informed citizens. This knowledge helps them grasp how laws are made, how government
  functions, and the importance of democratic participation, preparing them for active and
  engaged citizenship.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3366-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3366-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3366-3 ;
  curric:id "3366"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.379057Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

oakcurric:unit-3004
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What are our identities and our communities?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-are-our-identities-and-our-communities" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to the concepts of identities and communities and how
  these change over time and contexts."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about their identities and communities because they are
  beginning to understand the world around them. Understanding identities and community and
  diverse perspectives is crucial as their sense of belonging develops. This knowledge helps
  them appreciate how identities and communities change over time and helps to build a strong
  sense of interconnection and community.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3004-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3004-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3004-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3004-4 ;
  curric:id "3004"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.397215Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-identities-and-communities .

oakcurric:unit-3364
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What can we do about global problems?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-can-we-do-about-global-problems" ;
  rdfs:comment """Using a range of case studies from human rights to fracking and climate action,
  pupils consider how they can take responsible action to tackle some of the challenges
  currently facing society."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about global problems and challenges as they develop a
  broader awareness of the world. Understanding complex issues that interconnect people and the
  planet such as climate change, poverty and inequality is crucial for fostering a sense of
  shared responsibility. This knowledge empowers them as they consider the actions that
  governments and those in power can take. Alongside this they consider our own choices and
  decisions, and learn how they can be part of positive change, promoting a sense of
  collaboration, responsibility and global citizenship.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3364-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3364-2 ;
  curric:id "3364"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.500170Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-uk-and-the-wider-world .

oakcurric:unit-3358
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How does the media affect us?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-does-the-media-affect-us" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit students explore the roles and responsibilities of the media and the
  important role it plays within society."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about how the media affects us as they are increasingly
  exposed to various media and information sources. Understanding media influence, bias, and
  the importance of truth is crucial for developing critical thinking skills. This knowledge
  helps them discern reliable information, recognize bias, and understand the media's role in
  informing and shaping public opinion and holding those in power to account.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3358-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3358-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3358-3 ;
  curric:id "3358"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.510454Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-role-of-media-and-digital-democracy .

oakcurric:unit-3203
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How does local democracy work?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-does-local-democracy-work" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores the difference between local and national government. Pupils
  consider how governments are elected, the role of local councils and the key people within
  them."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about the differences between local and national government
  because they are starting to grasp how the political system works and impacts their lives.
  Understanding these differences is crucial for their civic awareness and participation in
  democracy. This knowledge helps them recognize the distinct roles and responsibilities of
  each level of government, fostering informed and active citizenship as they begin to engage
  with politcal and social ideas affecting communities and broader society.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3203-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3203-2 ;
  curric:id "3203"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.579849Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

oakcurric:unit-3478
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can we make a difference in our communities?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-we-make-a-difference-in-our-communities" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils examine what community means and the role it plays at their
  school. They explore what charities and NGOs do in their community and identify how they
  can become active citizens."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their learning of how they can make a positive difference in
  their communities this unit continues to develop pupils’ knowledge of social issues and the
  role citizens and organisations have in creating positive change. This knowledge helps pupils
  to understand how citizens can work together to improve communities and wider society and how
  they can make their voice heard by those in positions of power.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3478-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3478-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3478-3 ;
  curric:id "3478"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.597963Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-active-citizenship-making-a-positive-difference .

oakcurric:unit-3029
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What rights should all children have?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-rights-should-all-children-have" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces what rights we are all entitled to and how citizens can
  protect their rights. Pupils look in more depth at the right to health and the right to
  accurate information."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about the rights all children should have because they are
  developing a sense of justice and equity. Understanding children's rights is crucial for
  their awareness of global issues. This knowledge helps them recognize the importance of
  rights, advocate for themselves and others, and foster a fair and compassionate outlook as
  they develop as informed and responsible citizens.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3029-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3029-2 ;
  curric:id "3029"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.713564Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3369
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Why do people move around the world?"@en ;
  curric:slug "why-do-people-move-around-the-world" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider why people migrate, the impact it has on communities, whether
  migration should be controlled and what support is available to migrants."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about the different reasons why people move around the world
  as they develop a global perspective and understanding of migration. Building on earlier
  lessons about communities and global issues, understanding the complexity of migration is
  crucial for their awareness of diversity and change in communities and society. This
  knowledge helps them understand the economic, evironmental, social, and political factors
  driving migration, the complexities of migration globally as well as its impact on societies
  and the value of human rights and community cohesion.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3369-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3369-2 ;
  curric:id "3369"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.577177Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-uk-and-the-wider-world .

oakcurric:unit-3909
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How does the rule of law contribute to fairness?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-does-the-rule-of-law-contribute-to-fairness" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores how the rule of law operates in society. Pupils examine
  equality before the law, judicial independence, legal certainty and access to justice, and
  how these support fairness and trust."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops pupils’ understanding of the rule of law by moving from
  defining it to examining how it operates through systems and institutions. It builds on KS2
  knowledge of fairness and prepares pupils to evaluate how these systems function and can be
  challenged.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3909-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3909-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3909-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3909-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3909-5 ;
  curric:id "3909"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.687058Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 .

oakcurric:unit-3370
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can we manage money well?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-we-manage-money-well" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils explore how to look after their money considering the implications of
  borrowing, how they can keep track of their money, what saving options are available to
  them and what their rights are as a consumer."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils are becoming increasingly indepdent and will be considering future
  financial responsibilities. Learning to manage money now equips them with essential
  knolwledge and skills in relation to budgeting, saving, and making informed financial
  decisions in the future. They begin to connect personal financial choices and decisions with
  the understanding the economy, resources and their role in society as consumers, taxpayers
  and savers.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3370-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3370-2 ;
  curric:id "3370"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.000888Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-finance-and-the-economy .

oakcurric:unit-3204
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What is crime?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-is-crime" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider what crime is, what causes criminal behaviour and how communities
  can help prevent crime. They also explore whether youth crime is really as serious as the
  media portrays."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about what crime is because they are beginning to understand
  the rules and laws that help govern society. Understanding what constitutes a crime and its
  impact is crucial for their sense of justice and responsibility. This knowledge helps them
  recognize the importance of law, the consequences of crime, and the role of the justice
  system in protecting citizens including young people and maintaining order.""" ;
  curric:id "3204"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.079858Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3372
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can young people play an active role in democracy?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-young-people-play-and-active-role-in-democracy" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider what role they can play in their communities from school to local
  and national democracy."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Learning how young people can play an active role in democracy equips
  pupils with the knowledge and skills to engage in civic activities and influence
  decision-making. This unit is timely as it empowers pupils to understand how they can have a
  voice, exercise their rights and responsibilities, and the impact they can have on their
  communities and beyond.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3372-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3372-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3372-3 ;
  curric:id "3372"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.769949Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-active-citizenship-making-a-positive-difference .

